article.headline: Navy 85, Md.-Eastern Shore 61
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Chris Harris and Kaleo Kina scored 20 points apiece, and Navy shot 56 percent from 3-point range in an 85-61 win over Maryland-Eastern Shore on Saturday. Harris went 4-for-7 from behind the arc, and Kina hit three of his four 3-point attempts for the Midshipmen (4-8), who never trailed. Greg Sprink added 14 points and went 2-for-7 from beyond the arc, and reserve Adam Teague's nine points came on three 3-pointers. By contrast, the Hawks (2-11) went 4-for-21 from 3-point range, including a 2-for-10 performance from Ed Tyson, their leading scorer with 16 points. Reserve Josh Bright added 13 points, and Denzel Jackson had 11 points and 11 rebounds for Maryland-Eastern Shore. Navy jumped out to a 9-0 lead and led 41-23 at halftime. But the Hawks held the Midshipmen scoreless for the first 5:30 minutes of the second half, cutting the deficit to 41-35. Navy went 0-for-8 with six turnovers over that span. Kina, Teague and Harris hit 3-pointers that pushed the Mids' lead back to double figures. Navy also capitalized on mistakes, converting 15 UMES turnovers into 24 points.
